' description: 周期性总结与 UI Hand-off 简报按 provider 分流到 Claude / Deepseek / Codex oneshot
' last_updated: 2026-06-08
@startuml summary-handoff-provider-flow

title Summary / Hand-off provider 分流

actor "Summarizer scanAll" as Summarizer
actor "SessionHandOffSummarize IPC" as Handoff
participant "settingsStore" as Settings
participant "provider mapper" as Mapper
participant "adapterRegistry" as Registry
participant "claude-code adapter" as Claude
participant "deepseek-claude-code adapter" as Deepseek
participant "codex-cli adapter" as Codex
participant "oneshot prompt builders" as Prompt
database "summaryRepo and renderer preview" as Result

== 周期性总结 ==

Summarizer -> Settings: get(summaryProvider, summaryModel,\nsummaryReasoning, summaryTimeoutMs)
Settings --> Summarizer: provider = claude / deepseek / codex
Summarizer -> Mapper: providerToAdapterId(provider)
Mapper --> Summarizer: claude-code / deepseek-claude-code / codex-cli
Summarizer -> Registry: get(adapterId)
Registry --> Summarizer: adapter.summariseEvents
Summarizer -> Claude: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "summary")\nwhen provider=claude
Summarizer -> Deepseek: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "summary")\nwhen provider=deepseek
Summarizer -> Codex: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "summary")\nwhen provider=codex

alt claude provider
  Claude -> Prompt: buildSummarizePrompt(agentName="Claude")\nand buildSummarizeSystemPrompt("Claude")
  Claude --> Summarizer: compact summary
else deepseek provider
  Deepseek -> Deepseek: loadDeepseekClaudeEnv()
  Deepseek -> Prompt: buildSummarizePrompt(agentName="Deepseek")\nand buildSummarizeSystemPrompt("Deepseek")
  note right of Deepseek
    Deepseek reuses the Claude-family oneshot runner.
    It passes ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL / AUTH_TOKEN / model
    as an env overlay instead of mutating process.env.
  end note
  Deepseek --> Summarizer: compact summary
else codex provider
  Codex -> Prompt: buildSummarizePrompt(agentName="Agent")
  note right of Codex
    Codex is the only provider that consumes
    modelReasoningEffort from summaryReasoning.
  end note
  Codex --> Summarizer: compact summary
end

Summarizer -> Result: insert summary or fallback to\nassistant text / event stats on throw

== UI Hand-off 简报 ==

Handoff -> Settings: get(handOffProvider, handOffModel,\nhandOffReasoning)
Settings --> Handoff: provider = claude / deepseek / codex
Handoff -> Mapper: handOffProviderToAdapterId(provider)
Mapper --> Handoff: claude-code / deepseek-claude-code / codex-cli
Handoff -> Registry: get(summaryAdapterId)
Registry --> Handoff: summaryAdapter.summariseEvents
Handoff -> Registry: get(sourceSession.agentId)
Registry --> Handoff: sessionAdapter.createSession
note right of Handoff
  Stage 1 summary provider is settings-driven.
  Stage 2 spawn adapter stays source-session-driven.
  This keeps provider choice independent from the target session adapter.
end note

Handoff -> Claude: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "handoff")\nwhen provider=claude
Handoff -> Deepseek: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "handoff")\nwhen provider=deepseek
Handoff -> Codex: summariseEvents(cwd, events, "handoff")\nwhen provider=codex

alt claude provider
  Claude -> Prompt: buildHandoffPrompt(agentName="Claude")\nand buildHandoffSystemPrompt("Claude")
  Claude --> Handoff: structured brief
else deepseek provider
  Deepseek -> Deepseek: loadDeepseekClaudeEnv()
  Deepseek -> Prompt: buildHandoffPrompt(agentName="Deepseek")\nand buildHandoffSystemPrompt("Deepseek")
  Deepseek --> Handoff: structured brief
else codex provider
  Codex -> Prompt: buildHandoffPrompt(agentName="Agent")
  Codex --> Handoff: structured brief
end

Handoff -> Result: return modal preview summary\nthen SessionHandOffSpawn uses source adapter

@enduml
